# Frontend Cursor Rules - Angular Application

## Angular Specific Standards

### Component Architecture
- Use smart/dumb component pattern
- Keep components small and focused
- Implement OnPush change detection for performance
- Use ViewChild/ViewChildren sparingly

### State Management
- Use services for shared state
- Implement proper unsubscribe patterns
- Use BehaviorSubject for reactive state
- Avoid storing state in components

### Template Guidelines
- Use structural directives (*ngIf, *ngFor, *ngSwitch)
- Implement trackBy for performance
- Use safe navigation operators
- Keep templates under 50 lines

### Service Patterns
- Make services injectable and singleton
- Use HTTP interceptors for common operations
- Implement proper error handling
- Use environment configuration

### Styling Standards
- Use SCSS for styling
- Follow BEM methodology
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Implement responsive design patterns

### Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests for all components
- Test service methods thoroughly
- Use TestBed for component testing
- Mock external dependencies

### Performance Guidelines
- Use OnPush change detection
- Implement lazy loading for modules
- Optimize bundle size
- Use trackBy for lists

### Accessibility
- Include ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML
- Test with screen readers

### Code Quality
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Implement proper interfaces
- Use enums for constants
- Follow Angular style guide
